result.adr_address: 8 Finance St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: The French Window

reviews.text: Nice food. Not crowded. Also good if you only want to get a after work drink
Nice food and great environment for dinner

I usually come here with my client in last couple years, but I see the service and food are both getting worse recently. 

Understood Friday is busy during lunch time, but waiting 20 mins for the dessert is a bit unacceptable. Not to mention the rest I dislike...
Taste OK for the afternoon tea and they have a great view.

This is a very nice attempt at a restaurant located in IFC mall. 
Service was very good the night I was there and the seafood platter was excellent. 
It may be a little pricey around the wine list, but choose carefully and you will find a tasty bargain to enjoy with your meal. 
The view by the way is wonderful, so try and get a window seat.
